ðŸš€ Features
Task Manager

Add, complete, and delete tasks

Filter tasks: All, Active, Completed

Persistent storage using localStorage

Responsive design with Tailwind CSS

API Integration
Fetch posts from JSONPlaceholder

Theme Management
Light/Dark mode using React Context
Smooth transition between themes

Reusable Components
Button with multiple variants (primary, secondary, danger, success, warning)
Card for content layout
Navbar and Footer

ðŸ›  Setup Instructions
1. Prerequisites

Node.js v18 or higher

npm (comes with Node.js)

2. Clone the repository
git clone <your-repo-url>
cd <your-repo-folder>

3. Install dependencies
npm install

4. Run the development server
npm run dev

5. Build for production
npm run build

6. Deploying

You can deploy using Vercel, Netlify, or GitHub Pages

Example (Vercel):

Install Vercel CLI: npm i -g vercel

Run: vercel and follow prompts

Copy deployment URL to your README

